article.headline: E. Illinois 50, Jacksonville St. 48
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Jeremy Granger scored 18 points, including nine Eastern Illinois points in a row at one point, in a 50-48 victory over Jacksonville State on Saturday night. James Hollowell scored 10 and Ousmane Cisse grabbed a game-high 13 rebounds for the Panthers (8-5, 2-1 Ohio Valley). Nick Murphy led the Gamecocks (5-7, 1-1) with 12 points. Jay-R Strowbridge had 11 and Stephen Hall 10. Both teams shot poorly. Eastern Illinois was 19 of 53 (35.8 percent) and Jacksonville State even colder at 18 of 62 (29.0 percent). Jacksonville State led 27-20 at halftime, but a 7-minute drought to start the second half proved costly as Granger ran off nine straight Eastern points for a 31-29 lead. The lead changed hands three times in the final 5 minutes, but a 3-pointer by Tyler Laser with 2:25 left gave the Panthers a four-point edge, and they held on.
